# Body Composition Scans

Episodic machine reads (InBody, Karada Scan, etc.) — **not** daily vitals. Logged in app **Progress** tab; debrief paste includes scan block when a scan exists on that date.

## Cadence

- Target: **every 4–6 weeks** (app reminds at 5 weeks)
- Scan protocol: fasted AM preferred · no hard run 24h prior · same machine when possible · note hydration/state in notes field

## Fields that matter

| Field | Signal |
|-------|--------|
| Weight | Cross-check vs home scale — ±0.5 kg day-to-day is noise |
| Body fat % | Primary fat-loss trend (2+ scans) |
| Muscle mass (SMM / Karada muscle) | Deficit check — drop >0.5 kg between scans = protein or deficit too aggressive |
| Waist | Corroborates scale when weight stalls |
| Visceral fat | Secondary — ties to triglyceride goal |

## Coach interpretation

- **2+ scans required** before changing calories or protein targets based on composition
- Weight down + BF% down + muscle stable (−0.3 to +0.3 kg) = ideal deficit
- Weight flat + waist/BF% down = recomposition — do not slash calories further
- Muscle down >0.5 kg: anchor protein 150g+ for 2 weeks before cutting calories
- Compare to **Sep 2026 targets**: 70–71 kg · 18–19% BF · waist −2–4 in from baseline
- Dec 2024 InBody baseline: 74.8 kg · 26.5% BF · 30.9 kg SMM

## Monday vs scan

Monday check-in (weight, waist) stays weekly. Body comp scan is separate — do not merge into Monday vitals.
